Consultancy | Project Management | Training

When: Monday-Friday 23-27 July 2007, 10am-4pm
Where: Business Development Centre, 7-15 Greatorex Street, London E1 5NF
Who: Theatre &amp; performing arts oranisers/organisations
Cost: Free (for those based in Hackney, Newham &amp; Tower Hamlets)

This is an unique one-off programme covering all you need to know about
running a successful performing arts project or company!

In partnership with the Hackney Theatre Partnership, CIDA has devised a
highly interactive programme including training, guest speakers, panel
discussions and free tickets to top Hackney shows!

Our guest speakers will tell you how it all works in practice, and include
Ben Todd (Arcola Theatre), Nick Reed (Chats Palace), Charles Bishop (Theatre
Centre), Jo Carter (Immediate Theatre), and Monica Yam (freelance performing
arts consultant, previously with the Yellow Earth Theatre Company).

The programme will cover fundraising and sources of funding available,
working with venues, marketing, how to develop a great production plan and
making sure you are ready for the long-term!

Only a few places remaining, FREE for those based in Tower Hamlets, Hackney
or Newham.

The programme runs from Monday 23rd to Friday 27 July 2007, download the
full programme here.  To book your place please email Jessica Green at CIDA
or call 020 7247 4710.
